      "message": "Can we simplify this to:\n\n   proxy \u003d proxyProvider-\u003efindOrCreateproxyByUniqueKey(key);\n   if (!proxy) {\n      proxy \u003d make_bmp_proxy(proxyProvider, bitmap, ct, mipmapped, \n                             SkBackingFit::kExact, SkBudgeted::kYes);\n      if (!proxy) {\n         return {};\n      }\n\n      SkASSERT(mipmapped \u003d\u003d GrMipmapped::kNo || \n               proxy-\u003emipmapped() \u003d\u003d GrMipmapped::kYes);\n      installKey(proxy.get());\n   }\n\n   SkASSERT(proxy);\n   swizzle \u003d caps-\u003egetReadSwizzle(proxy-\u003ebackendFormat(), ct);\n   if (mipmapped \u003d\u003d GrMipmapped::kNo || proxy-\u003emipmapped() \u003d\u003d GrMipmapped::kYes) {\n      return {{std::move(proxy), kTopLeft_GrSurfaceOrigin, swizzle}, ct};\n   }\n\n   SkASSERT(mipmapped \u003d\u003d GrMipmapped::kYes);\n   ...\n\nAfter writing this out, not 100% sure if it\u0027s that much simpler, but it does \nonly update the swizzle, return the non-mipmap-gen once, and I find the failed-to\nmake proxy return easier to spot in this case. But it\u0027s a little weird the way I\nhave the make_bmp_proxy path assert we\u0027ll hit the next if condition to return.\n\nSo an alternative that reads better for the failed-to-make case would be:\n\n   proxy \u003d proxyProvider-\u003efindOrCreateproxyByUniqueKey(key);\n   if (proxy) {\n      swizzle \u003d caps-\u003egetReadSwizzle(proxy-\u003ebackendFormat(), ct);\n      if (mipmapped \u003d\u003d GrMipmapped::kNo || \n          proxy-\u003emipmapped() \u003d\u003d GrMipmapped::kYes) {\n         return {{std::move(proxy), kTopLeft_GrSurfaceOrigin, swizzle}, ct};\n      }\n   }\n   if (!proxy) {\n      proxy \u003d make_bmp_proxy(proxyProvider, bitmap, ct, mipmapped,\n                             SkBackingFit::kExact, SkBudgeted::kYes);\n      if (!proxy) {\n         return {};\n      }\n      \n      swizzle \u003d caps-\u003egetReadSwizzle(proxy-\u003ebackendFormat(), ct);\n      SkASSERT(mipmapped \u003d\u003d GrMipmapped::kNo || \n               proxy-\u003emipmapped() \u003d\u003d GrMipmapped::kYes);\n      installKey(proxy.get());\n      return {{std::move(proxy), kTopLeft_GrSurfaceOrigin, swizzle}, ct};\n   }\n\n   SkASSERT(proxy);",
